Bethhaccerem: Beth-haccerem was a town of Judah, situated on a mountain,
between Jerusalem and Tekoa, according to Jerome on Jer. 6. Dr. Pococke
conjectures that the Mountain of the Franks, called also the Mount of
Bethulia, from a village of that name near it, west-north-west of Tekoa,
is the ancient Beth-haccerem; the position of which seems to agree with
the citadel of Herodium, built by Herod, on a moderate-sized hill, sixty
furlongs from Jerusalem. [Jer 6:1](../../../bib/kjv/jer006.htm#001.md)

