the goldsmiths: The word tzeraphim may denote smiths, or refiners, or
persons that worked in metals of any kind; but it is generally
understood of those who worked in gold. From the remotest period of the
history of the Jews, they had artists in all the elegant and ornamental
trades; and it appears that goldsmiths, apothecaries, and merchants were
formed into companies in the time of Nehemiah. [Neh
3:8](../../../bib/kjv/neh003.htm#008.md), [Neh
3:31](../../../bib/kjv/neh003.htm#031.md)

